WEBVTT

00:08:58.040 --> 00:09:00.216
Enter personality tests.

00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:04.336
They give us that language,
which is why so many companies love them.

00:09:04.360 --> 00:09:06.576
Of all the workplaces I've visited,

00:09:06.600 --> 00:09:10.096
there's one where personality tests
seem to be indispensable.

00:09:10.120 --> 00:09:11.696
It's called Bain & Company,

00:09:11.720 --> 00:09:14.576
a hugely successful
management consulting firm.

00:09:14.600 --> 00:09:18.256
They hire smart people
to help fix other companies' problems.

00:09:18.280 --> 00:09:20.536
Mitt Romney is a former CEO there

00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:24.680
and recently Glassdoor named them
the best place to work in all of America.

00:09:26.040 --> 00:09:29.576
The leaders at Bain think
personality is pretty important,

00:09:29.600 --> 00:09:33.776
so important, in fact, that before
new hires even learn how to do their jobs,